args:
Volk attacks a nobleman, Kai Yan makes war on
a village, and Ayaha and Otoha head for the
border. The members of Agito then meet up
with Ciella, who had been waiting for them all.
A few days prior to the prince's party\narriving at the mountain path...
Are you enjoying this taste of the pain\nsuffered by those who have not?
Why are you...doing this to me...?\nI make donations...so all in this town\nmight live in comfort...
Rich people such as yourself blithely\ndistribute false salvation to the swarming\nmasses of have-nots.
In this way does the bond between weak\nand the strong go on...and on...AND ON!
Thus do the strong remain so throughout\nthe years—throughout the CENTURIES!

Do you know where the strong are?
They live a blessed existence on high,
untroubled and in bliss from the moment
their mothers birth them into this world.
Meanwhile, the weak crawl in the mud,\nfeeble, alone, and invisible so you need\nfeel nothing for their true plight.
The weak are never seen; not when they\nare cast aside, not when they are misused,\nand not when they die cold and alone.
But now it is time to reunite with\nZacharias's son and all those who\nstand with him spewing false hope...
＂That's the fresh fish I bought at the\nmarket today, dear! Have some!＂
＂Eh heh heh! How does it taste?＂
＂Scrumptious! You're the best chef\nin these parts, Mama!＂
Yeah, I know—but we have to get going.
No, we're fine! Let's play a little more!
But then we will be late.
Fine then. We'll find some new dolls to\nplay with when we get there!
Yes. Let us be on our way.\n...Oh, oops, my hands are dirty.\nLooks like this doll is broken.
Please stop! If you take that much food,\nwe'll all starve to death!
Quit yer moanin' and hand it over!
Blimey, who the hell is this?!
You look to have a fighting spirit, sir!\nPlease save us from these brigands!
Weaklings who cannot protect themselves\ngather together to exult in peaceable lives.\nIt is a most unsightly thought.
You have not earned the right of survival,\nand so shall be destroyed utterly.
Saaay, I like the cut of yer jib, stranger!\nWhat say ya throw yer lot in with us?
You shall be culled as well.
You take from those weaker than yourself.\nYour spirit is frail. Useless.

This land is filled by those who avoid true
conflict and devote themselves only to the
easy battle. There is no value in such a
thing. Now accept your ending with grace.
All who populate this continent are feeble.

Spoiled, the people grow fleshy in both
body and mind. Ere long will they be
consumed by nature and consigned
to the butcher's midden.
This, too, is because they were deceived\nby false peace and renounced discipline.\nSuch people are beyond excuse.
The one who summoned us here yet\nruns late. How truly hopeless...
Those who wish to do so, at any rate.
That's rather non-committal.\n...Well, speak of the devils.
What a stroke of luck that you would have\nthe good grace to come when called.
Not much else to do considering HE is the\none who called us. Isn't that right, Oto?
We certainly wouldn't be here with these\npeople otherwise. Right, Aya?
Yes. But luckily, we'll be able to\nbreak the empty little dolly!
I can't WAIT to play with my new doll!
I will cull all who spread\nthe way of heresy.
Well, that just leaves one more.\nWhere could he be, mmm?
Yes, he should be here by now.
Indeed. Still, we now await only the\ntrue form and the pretender. Soon,\nwe will witness a very special despair.
I can hardly wait for the moment when we\ntear that seventh scion disguise from his\nmiserable face! Aaaah ha ha ha ha ha!
